scopecontent.value:
AFTER SORROW is an evening-length dance theater work composed of four solos performed by Muna Tseng. The first three pieces - L'Histoire Chinoise, Whispers of the Stone and 98.6: a convergence in 15 minutes - form a suite about loss and the obligations owed family and friends; the fourth piece After Sorrow (Viet Nam) is about the legacy of war.

After Sorrow is the third part of Ping Chong's East/West Series.
